#: ../../../contributing/internals.md:30
msgid "Theme build process"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/internals.md:32
msgid ""
"Furo's build process uses {pypi}`sphinx-theme-builder` and Webpack. Running "
"`webpack` in the repository root will compile the theme's CSS and JS assets "
"(`src/furo/assets/`) into the correct final files (inside `src/furo/theme/"
"furo/static`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/internals.md:34
msgid ""
"When generating a wheel (eg: for upload, or for installing from a source "
"distribution), `sphinx-theme-builder` will use {pypi}`nodeenv` to create an "
"isolated NodeJS installation (using the system NodeJS version if it matches "
"the requirements)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/internals.md:36
msgid ""
"Thus, the source distribution does not contain the compiled JS artifacts and "
"wheel distribution does. Both contain the original SASS/JS source code for "
"Furo. Using the SASS/JS source code of Furo is consider \"unstable\" under "
"the stability policy."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/internals.md:38
msgid "How stuff works"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/internals.md:40
msgid "Sidebar Navigation Tree"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/internals.md:42
msgid ""
"This is was really tricky to get right. It is essentially a pure-CSS port of "
"the Just the Docs theme's sidebar navigation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/internals.md:44
msgid ""
"Each list item has a fixed height and a different color on hover. Items with "
"a subtree underneath have a hidden checkbox, that is triggered when clicking "
"the item. The checkbox holds the state of \"expanded vs collapsed\", which "
"is used in the CSS to show the subtree appropriately. The checkbox is "
"automatically checked if it is for the current page, or a parent of the "
"current page."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/internals.md:46
msgid ""
"There was a painful amount of tweaking the CSS to get the subtrees to look "
"just right even when there's long text and lots of content/subtrees etc. It "
"works now, and that's all I care about."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/internals.md:48
msgid "Contents sidebar"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/internals.md:50
msgid ""
"This uses the `toc` variable that's provided by Sphinx. There's some CSS to "
"hide the top-level bullet referring to this page's title. The rest of the "
"tree is stylised without much complexity."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/internals.md:52
msgid ""
"The fancy bit is that Gumshoe.js is used to highlight the currently active "
"heading (which heading is the content at the top pixel under). This is "
"combined with some custom JS to scroll to the currently active heading in "
"the toctree, which results in the contents sidebar scrolling with the user "
"as they go."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/internals.md:54
msgid "CSS variables for customisation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/internals.md:56
msgid ""
"This is pretty much the \"USP\" of this theme. In `src/furo/theme/furo/"
"partials/_head_css_variables.html`, the user provided CSS variables are "
"translated and written into each page's HTML. This is set up, such that "
"these declarations overrides any other declarations made in the CSS of the "
"theme."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/internals.md:58
msgid ""
"This essentially allows the user to control the values of the CSS variables, "
"and hence control how the theme looks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/internals.md:60
msgid "`furo-demo` directive"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/internals.md:62
msgid ""
"This directive was written to make it easier to write the examples used in "
"the [Reference](../reference/index) section. The way it works is pretty "
"straightforward really:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/internals.md:64
msgid ""
"It only works in MyST documents, since it performs an in-place substitution."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/internals.md:65
msgid ""
"It takes the contents of the block, splits it at \"+++\" into Markdown and "
"reStructuredText snippets."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/internals.md:66
msgid ""
"For both of these, it renders a tab that has a code block containing the "
"snippet followed by the actual code itself."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/internals.md:67
msgid ""
"This is carefully crafted to ensure that things are evaluated correctly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/internals.md:69
msgid ""
"This approach has significant limitations however, since the A/B comparision "
"format means that it is not directly usable to showcase functionality that "
"is different between the two."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/internals.md:71
msgid ""
"For that, we keep one of the snippets empty, which thanks to a conditional, "
"results in the tab for that language (MyST or reST) not being rendered."
msgstr ""
